# Built by dot-update.d/ollama as the `code` model - used via the `aider`
# wrapper function (.zshrc.d/aider) over http://llm.home, or directly with
# `ollama run code`.
#
# Different job than `offload` (Modelfile.offload): that one is for cheap,
# low-stakes tasks handed down from Claude to save money. This one is the
# fallback for when Claude itself isn't reachable at all (offline, rate
# limited) and coding work still has to happen - so it's tuned for
# correctness over speed, on the biggest model this box can reasonably run.
#
# qwen2.5-coder:14b's q4 weights (~9GB) are already bigger than the 8GB
# card, so this partially spills to system RAM - slower than a model that
# fits fully in VRAM, but still the strongest coding model this hardware
# can run at a usable pace. Check the actual split with `ollama ps`
# (PROCESSOR column) after loading it.
#
# No SYSTEM block here - dot-update.d/ollama assembles it at build time from
# ~/.claude/context/{workbench,garden}.md (the same identity/approach layer
# a real Claude Code session gets via SessionStart hooks) plus
# code-system-addendum.md in this directory, WHEN priv-config is present on
# this box. It isn't by default - this is the "home" account on a shared
# household machine, not a personal dev box, so it doesn't get chase's
# priv-config cloned here without that being asked for explicitly. Falls
# back to addendum-only if those files are missing. `offload` skips this
# layer entirely regardless - it's meant to be fast and low-stakes, and
# 150+ lines of philosophy on every quick call works against that.

FROM qwen2.5-coder:14b

PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
